  "text": "The findings identify risk factors of the shared component of depression and symptoms of anxiety disorders (i.e., negative emotionality). Future research should also identify risk factors of the unique components of these aversive emotional states. A large portion of the variance in depression symptoms is shared with many of the anxiety disorders (i.e., negative emotionality), but each of these aversive emotional states has unique components that must be considered [CITATION_1] . For example, low positive affect (i.e., joy, enthusiasm, engagement) is a unique component of depression, that is, it does not appear to be associated with generalized anxiety, panic, or trauma [CITATION_2] .",
